init<br />&gt;code resets pg0[0] to the original value so any change here is<br />&gt;ignored.  In the second case, pg0[0] does not seem to be the correct<br />&gt;PTE either (swapper_pg_dir[0] is cleared in paging_init).<br /><br />It's being set because it's being used to test the WP bit - if we don't<br />set it then we couldn't return to the code that tests it.  See the file<br />arch/i386/mm/init.c (and the "wp_works_ok" variable in particular). <br /><br />This is all just to support the i386 WP-doesn't-work-in-supervisor-mode<br />bug,<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
